< Review>
They do an amazing job at Nail 2000 of UTC! I've only done solar nails and gel/shellac nails. They are known for their shellac nails and for a good reason. They stay on, don't chip, and look amazing for at least 2 weeks. They are very meticulous in the way they do their manicures. They ask many questions about your preferences and don't take it personally if you'd like them to change something. They put on two base coats and top coats as well as multiple color coats. They also put sunscreen on your hands when you're using the UV lights! I love that touch of thoughtfulness. My nails rarely ever break when I've got shellac due to the many coats of polish. It's also reasonably priced. They are also known for doing ombre nails. I wouldn't go anywhere else!<//Review>

<Time>1597039519187<//Time>< text>
The staff was mostly professional and friendly and they were enforcing covid precautions inside.  It was a nice stylish ambiance inside but way too dark. We had to use the flashlights on our phones to see any of the color options.  The prices are a bit high for the pedicures but they had a new "multi pieces set" type of options like aloe gel and other scented gelatin like substances.  They had beautiful color options and a new "cat eye" polish which is 12.00 extra. There were a few things bothersome.  Such as seeming like they were hurrying to finish the actual process but then there was a bit of a wait between manicure and pedicures in my group.  Also it seemed like they weren't listening to the wants of the client design or shape wise. The finished product of the nails my daughter got done were sloppily done and not very good looking.<//text>

< review>
Recently bought some after-market driving lights and many auto shops were reluctant to wire them up.   One shop suggested a stereo specialist which I hadn't even thought of. Pro Inet is that and much more. With newer cars having all kinds of computer systems and air bag technology, the average Joe is going to be in over his head trying to wire almost anything. Scott at Pro Inet said "no problem" and that they were  busy ( a good thing ) but to come by in a few days and they'd take care of it. C J , the tech guru, made it seem like a walk in the park to wire the lights. I could have spent all day on it and probably would have lit up the air bags along with crashing the computers while it took him about 45 minutes to wire up a very clean job. These guys know their stuff. Any electrical in the future, they'll be my first call.< /review>

<username>Laszlo Bertalan<//username><gmap_id>0x80d94e18e6d2034b:0xef7ace6641995f07</gmap_id><Rate>4</Rate>< text>
My wife and I made a same-day appointment for a couple's massage and they were able to accommodate us without any problem. Since it was our first time here we opted for the $55 Happy Head massage (head, shoulders, arms, neck, and back) which was 1 hour. The environment was relaxing enough in my opinion and the staff was friendly, however, it seems that many of them don't speak English very well. That being said, my masseuse was very experienced with strong hands to work out the knots in my shoulders. We came out very relaxed and refreshed. One thing that caused me to remove 1 star is that when finished the masseuse stands at the entrance expecting a tip, which is a bit awkward and should be reconsidered by management. Aside from that it was a great experience and we'll be back when we need to relieve some tension.< /text>

Sometimes you just have a craving for a snack in between lunch and dinner.  You don't want it to be too heavy.  In times like these, a spam musubi from L and L hits the spot!  Warm rice with nice hot spray on top.  Put a little bit of sricha sauce, you have a winner.  L and L is a no frills place that makes generous portions of food from the Hawaiian islands.  Good BBQ items.  Staff is wearing masks and there is a bottle of hand sanitizer laying around.< /Review>

<time>1599361045531</time>< Rating>
5</Rating>
< text>
We arrived on a holiday weekend at about 5pm and had to wait for about 20 minutes to be seated. Our seat was on the upper patio in the shade (we were given the option to pick). The host who seated us was friendly. Our server promptly greeted us and was very genuine and kind. He told us the specials and gave us his recommendations. The menu had a lot of seafood but also steaks, pastas, sandwiches, a burger, and other choices for a great variety. I had the Mai Tai which was delicious. I also ordered the Ribeye which was one of the recommendations and it was delicious. The complimentary bread was soft and flavorful. The food was all a great value for the price our service remained top notch with our order all coming out in a timely manner. I would definitely recommend checking Tony P's out if you are in Marina Del Rey.<//text>

< review>
This place is fantastic - food, service, atmosphere!

We went for happy hour, so we ordered potato skins, sliders, Mac n cheese, nachos, and some drinks.  Every item was a decent serving and tasted great.  Their drinks were also good! They don't rip you off on the alcohol.  I also liked that their happy hour menu had many items to choose from.  It's disappointing when there's only 3 items to pick from at other places- not the case here.

I would 100% go again especially because I got to watch the Dodger game! And easy to find street parking.</review>

<user_id>104250383382489482539< /user_id>< name>
Jennifer Miele< /name>
<time>1560553593185<//time><rating>4<//rating>< review>
This place has a great atmosphere, friendly service, and great views if you're in the dining section. My husband went to watch the NBA final game last night, and had a great time. We sat in the bar area, which was buzzing with excited sports fans. We ate during happy hour, and while the appetizers were only $7.95, the food was a bit bland, but we didn't have any entrees, so I couldn't speak for any signature dishes. Overall, it was enjoyable and my husband and son mentioned a few more times today, how much they enjoyed the crowd and staff at Tony P's. Definitely recommend, but maybe try a seafood dish, which I'm sure will be better than the nachos, spinach- artichoke dip, and calamari. <Name>Jennifer Miele<//Name>< review>
This place has a great atmosphere, friendly service, and great views if you're in the dining section. My husband went to watch the NBA final game last night, and had a great time. We sat in the bar area, which was buzzing with excited sports fans. We ate during happy hour, and while the appetizers were only $7.95, the food was a bit bland, but we didn't have any entrees, so I couldn't speak for any signature dishes. Overall, it was enjoyable and my husband and son mentioned a few more times today, how much they enjoyed the crowd and staff at Tony P's. Definitely recommend, but maybe try a seafood dish, which I'm sure will be better than the nachos, spinach- artichoke dip, and calamari. The quesadilla was decent and so were the potato skins.<//review>

<user_id>101128729472721895532<//user_id>< Name>
Tokoro B</Name>
<Date>1564878940110<//Date><rating>4<//rating>< review>
An institution in Marina del Rey. Nice outdoor eating space. The menu is pretty typical - steaks, fish, salads, pizza. There is an extensive selection of beers. Service is generally good. Almost everything is garlicky, even when a "no garlic" request is made. The fish is often frozen - ask if you want something fresh and local. (Salmon is farmed, not wild, and comes from either the Pacific Northwest or the Atlantic.) The food is fine, but not spectacular. We eat here often because Grandma loves it, and she can get her bourbon. I like the bouillabaisse and the quinoa and beet salad.</review>
<pictures>None<//pictures>< Resp>
{'time': 1565115935038, 'text': 'Hi Tokoro, thanks for coming into Tony P\'s! glad you enjoyed your self!. Just a little FYI, we offer 4 to 5 different fresh fish daily. "never frozen" We are so glad your grandma loves our bourbon selection!! See you soon.'}</Resp>

I've been coming here since before it was Tony P when it was Charlie Brown's. This is always a nice place to visit.  Food is always will prepare and the view from the deck is beautiful. I lived local for many decades and live in another state now but always come here when I am in town.< /Review>

<date>1564878940110< /date><Rate>4<//Rate>< Text>
An institution in Marina del Rey. Nice outdoor eating space. The menu is pretty typical - steaks, fish, salads, pizza. There is an extensive selection of beers. Service is generally good. Almost everything is garlicky, even when a "no garlic" request is made. The fish is often frozen - ask if you want something fresh and local. (Salmon is farmed, not wild, and comes from either the Pacific Northwest or the Atlantic.) The food is fine, but not spectacular. We eat here often because Grandma loves it, and she can get her bourbon. I like the bouillabaisse and the quinoa and beet salad.<//Text>

<UserId.>102644440786565505002<//UserId.><user_name>Lance Powell</user_name><Date>1551468560932<//Date><Rate>3</Rate>< review>
Tony P's is the last of several institutional restaurants that have not evolved beyond the 90s.

Its location to on the water is choice, however it bookends mediocre food and decent service.

Their prices are fairly typical for restaurants along its row with dishes landing between $13 & $24 dollars depending on the dish.

If you are a sports fanatic, the bar area is special. It's Bill for sports enthusiasts and can be a lot of fun depending on the games and energy at the people watching.< /review>

As a couple that frequents restaurant's on a very regular basis, I must say that Tony P's really is one of the best all around places to really enjoy. Everything from the parking to the ambiance, the food and most importantly the staff is great. My wife and I have always enjoyed our time at Tony P's. We have been most fortunate to have one of the of the nicest servers on our several recent visits, by the name of Kalie M, who truly adds to our evening. Kalie is so personalbe and truly is concerned that you are having a great meal.  Everything about the place is EASY and friendly. The staff always accommodates us with a smile. If for instance I need a refill or something of that nature, and our server is occupied elsewhere, undoubtedly there is someone at your service. You don't get "it's not my table" attitude.Truly what all restaurants should strive to be. Very well priced offering a very diverse menu. Take the whole family or just a romantic dinner for two over looking the fabulous yachts in the marina. Thank you Tony P's!!<//Review>

<text>The food is mediocre at best- they definitely are relying on their great view of the marina to get people to come in, because it isn‚Äôt the food.
I ordered the fish and chips and added a wedge salad for $4.75. The wedge salad was just lettuce, tomato, and watery blue cheese. When I asked about the onions and the bacon the server said that isn‚Äôt available on the add-on wedge, only the appetizer wedge ($10.95). Nowhere on the menu does it call that out. The flavor really comes from those components mixing with the others. I would recommend skipping the add-on wedge- it was flavorless. It didn‚Äôt even have blue cheese crumbles to help boost the flavor.
Two people at my table ordered the French Onion Soup and they described it as ‚Äúunderwhelming.‚Äù
The fish and chips were decent- not a ton of flavor but tasted fresh, the breading was a little doughy. I substituted the fries for veggies- the veggies were good and you get a large portion (I bet if they scaled down their veggie portion slightly they‚Äôd be able to afford to put some onions and bacon on the wedge salad :) )
Someone at my table had the mahi-mahi and really enjoyed it.
Another person in my party had the salmon- it was cooked nicely but again did not have a lot of flavor.
Our server at the end of the meal explained that an 18% gratuity was added on because ‚ÄúI have to split the tips with my co-workers.‚Äù That really left a bad taste in our mouths because when I said ‚Äúyou have to split it from this table?‚Äù He said ‚Äúyeah we have to tip out.‚Äù I worked as a server through high school and college- tipping out is par for the course. At every restaurant I‚Äôve worked for there is some form of tipping out your back of house, bar, hostess, bussers, etc. It wasn‚Äôt because we were a large group so he had to split the tips with his co-workers, it‚Äôs because that is what you do as a server since they are the ones helping you satisfy your customers.
Two of the people in our party own a boat in the marina and were looking for another restaurant to frequent nearby, but based on last night‚Äôs experience will not be returning to Tony P‚Äôs.</text>< pictures>
None< /pictures>
< Response>
{'time': 1555364328305, 'text': 'HI Amy, thanks for coming into Tony P\'s. I am sorry about the confusion on the wedge salad. We do offer 2 different wedge salads. One is an add on to an entree (Iceburg wedge, tomatoes, red onions and dressing. $4.75) and one is on the entree salad section (Iceburg wedge, tomatoes, red onions, smoked bacon, crumbled blue cheese and dressing $10.95). We will retrain the salad cook who needs to stir the blue cheese dressing that we make in house, that is full of chunks of blue cheese. I apologize that you didn\'t get that. Regarding the 18% gratuity which is added on to parties of 6 or more. The server didn\'t do a very good job of explaining it to you. Like most restaurants, we add gratuity to tables of 6 or more people. Since you were a server before you understand this policy. Please e-mail me your server\'s name (tony@tonyps.com) and what time you came in. If you do not agree with the added gratuity, please let the manager know and we would take it off.  Our servers "tip out" to the Bussers, Food Runners and Bartenders that help them service your table. They do not share their tips with any other servers. All of this should not have anything to do with you getting great service when you come in. It is all house keeping issues on our side of the restaurant business and I am sorry if you were inconvenienced. Anytime you come into Tony P\'s, and you are not satisfied with service or food please let our managers know. We want everyone to have a great experience.'}<//Response>

< review>
As a couple that frequents restaurant's on a very regular basis, I must say that Tony P's really is one of the best all around places to really enjoy. Everything from the parking to the ambiance, the food and most importantly the staff is great. My wife and I have always enjoyed our time at Tony P's. We have been most fortunate to have one of the of the nicest servers on our several recent visits, by the name of Kalie M, who truly adds to our evening. Kalie is so personalbe and truly is concerned that you are having a great meal.  Everything about the place is EASY and friendly. The staff always accommodates us with a smile. If for instance I need a refill or something of that nature, and our server is occupied elsewhere, undoubtedly there is someone at your service. You don't get "it's not my table" attitude.Truly what all restaurants should strive to be. Very well priced offering a very diverse menu. Take the whole family or just a romantic dinner for two over looking the fabulous yachts in the marina. Thank you Tony P's!!<//review>

<time>1547477446607<//time><user_name>Rob Savory</user_name><Resp>{'time': 1547492265277, 'text': 'Hi Rob, thank you so much for your kind words! Please say hi next time you come in!'}< /Resp><user>104255834287005683761< /user><Review>I've come here many times and always have a great time. The outdoor seating is ideal for datenight as there is a view of the marina (there are heat lamps) and all the boats and the marina are lit up. Great to watch the sunset. It is a beautiful ambiance for either a table for two or the whole family.
There is also a bar with lots of beers on tap and the bartenders make great cocktails too! This place is set up with tons of TVs so that every football game is available to watch during the season, or any sport for that matter. I think I come here for every big sport event; football playoffs, basketball plays, Sunday football brunch, and baseball playoffs.
The food is great. I love getting the cajun penne pasta; great portion size for your money and tastes amazing. The fish and chips are the best I think I've ever had and there is a tuxedo cake desert which is a must every time I go here.
The wait staff is very friendly and I don't think I have ever sat long for any help or service. They are attentive and approachable. I highly recommend this place to anyone who lives in the area (or doesn't) or someone visiting and staying near LAX. Won't be disappointed.< /Review></record>

<Review>I have been coming here for over 15 years! Almost everytime I've been here, the staff is friendly and informed of their menu and selections. Timing to me is important in a restaurant, you don't like to be pushed through and out the door, and this establishment has never done that, actually the opposite there have been several times a group and myself come here and seriously feel like we at grandmas house, relaxing and down to earth environment. <Text>Want to party in your mouth? Go to Tony P's Dockside Grill and this is definitely what you will not get. I opened door number two and my tastebuds were sent to detention instead

Ordered:
Seafood ‚ÄúGuac‚Äù Tail
Florida rock shrimp, blue crab meat, fresh pico de gallo, avocado and lime. Warm corn chips.

Not much seafood. Lots of avocado and onions.

Ordered:
Salmon and Shrimp Combo
Grilled salmon and grilled garlic shrimp, citrus beurre blanc sauce.

Much too bland for my liking. Tried changing the flavor with extra citrus beurre blanc sauce. Big mistake.

Ordered:
Clam Chowder
OK, this might be the only thing that was worth eating.

Best part:

<Text>(Translated by Google) It is a cheap and delicious grill shop.
When I was walking along the yacht harbor, I found a shop full of many customers in the evening, so I entered.

Nearby are luxury resort apartments.

Salmon salad, pasta, and steak are just the right volume for a Japanese person to eat with four people.

All are delicious and reasonable.

After entering the store and opening the right door, there was a huge BAR space.

The store owner donated to various places, and a lot of letters of appreciation were displayed at the entrance.
